00:03:25.980 --> 00:03:32.249
but it is one style of beer and this style
of beer, it makes up 95% of what we Americans

00:03:32.249 --> 00:03:33.249
drink as beer.

00:03:33.249 --> 00:03:37.020
&gt;&gt;Hallie: And, that is, that is a light lager,
so a light lager is what you are generally

00:03:37.020 --> 00:03:42.560
used to. Your Coronas, your Heinekens, your
Budweisers, your Coors, this is all one style.

00:03:42.560 --> 00:03:47.790
So , you know we try to tell people, you know,
if you if you haven't gotten into craft beer,

00:03:47.790 --> 00:03:51.739
you've probably only had one style of beer,
a lager or a light pilsner, which is which

00:03:51.739 --> 00:03:56.950
is also a lager; and that would be like having
one kind of wine for the rest of your life.

00:03:56.950 --> 00:03:57.950
So it's like --

00:03:57.950 --> 00:03:58.950
&gt;&gt;Christina: --I'll have a white zinfandel
please.

00:03:58.950 --> 00:04:01.109
&gt;&gt;Hallie: Yeah, and that is it. Just like
saying, l'll, I'll just have white zinfandel

