for the rest of my life. That is it, done.
Doesn't matter what I'm eating, doesn't matter

00:04:04.720 --> 00:04:09.099
what I'm in the mood for; so, we're, we're
trying you know to show you as we go through

00:04:09.099 --> 00:04:13.549
this beer journey together. Um, we'll show
you that there is so many different flavors

00:04:13.549 --> 00:04:17.980
in beer and so you can have more variety and
that's what excites us about craft beer. That's

00:04:17.980 --> 00:04:22.350
why we wrote the book. That's why we got into
it. There's such a great vast variety of flavors

00:04:22.350 --> 00:04:23.350
in beer.

00:04:23.350 --> 00:04:27.389
&gt;&gt;Christina: You know we get all the time,
"I'm not a beer drinker....I don't drink beer.....I'm

00:04:27.389 --> 00:04:30.430
not a beer drinker" and we call those people,
we say that they are in denial....

00:04:30.430 --> 00:04:31.490
[audience laughter]

00:04:31.490 --> 00:04:35.199
&gt;&gt;Christina: because there, there is a beer
out there for everyone, so maybe some people

00:04:35.199 --> 00:04:41.020
just haven't found it yet. Because like Hallie
said there are 150 different styles of beer.

00:04:41.020 --> 00:04:45.210
This beer can taste like chocolate, it can
taste like fruit, it can taste like citrus,

00:04:45.210 --> 00:04:50.650
it can taste toasty, nutty, it, it runs the
gamut as far as flavor profile is concerned.

00:04:50.650 --> 00:04:55.370
And, it it goes to show if, if you have tried
95% of the beers that are out there. If you've

00:04:55.370 --> 00:04:58.470
tried Beks, you've tried Heineken, you've
tried Coors, you've tried Budweiser, not that

00:04:58.470 --> 00:05:02.550
these are bad breweries; I am just saying
if you've tried all of those beers and you

00:05:02.550 --> 00:05:07.760
don't like a pilsner style lager, you are
going to deduce that you don't like beer because

00:05:07.760 --> 00:05:12.000
you've tried everything that is out there
and you don't like it. You know we get a lot

00:05:12.000 --> 00:05:16.150
of women all the time that, I don't like beer,
I don't want to drink beer. Well it is because

00:05:16.150 --> 00:05:17.150
they're --

00:05:17.150 --> 00:05:18.150
[inaudible comment from the audience]

00:05:18.150 --> 00:05:21.919
&gt;&gt;Hallie: that was a pretty mean, uh --

00:05:21.919 --> 00:05:28.259
&gt;&gt;Christina: I had one person in mind; I had
one person in mind. Um, but a lot of times

00:05:28.259 --> 00:05:33.259
you know women don't like hoppy, bitter beer.
Sometimes they do. I happen to and I know

00:05:33.259 --> 00:05:37.300
you do too Hallie; but a lot of times women
don't like that bitter flavor in beer and

00:05:37.300 --> 00:05:42.461
all the pilsners have that little bitter flavor
and so a lot of women then deduce that they

00:05:42.461 --> 00:05:43.461
don't like beer.

00:05:43.461 --> 00:05:45.690
So we are starting out with the Budweiser.

