use wine glasses. We don't have those today,
but we will use a glass that you would use

00:06:02.810 --> 00:06:09.159
just, just for a Pinot Noir, whatever. So,
just swirl the glass, get your nose down in

00:06:09.159 --> 00:06:13.409
there, like way down in there to get familiar
with your beer. See what you pick up on your

00:06:13.409 --> 00:06:18.139
nose. If it is not pretty that is ok because
you know, this is a particular kind of beer;

00:06:18.139 --> 00:06:23.939
so maybe you don't like what you smell. And
then take a sip and kinda let it, you know,

00:06:23.939 --> 00:06:28.479
move around in your mouth, let a little air
in just you would when you are tasting wine.

00:06:28.479 --> 00:06:32.470
Get, get your initial flavors, Yeah, make
that sound, that weird sound and that weird

00:06:32.470 --> 00:06:38.180
face that Christina is making right now um
and then take a second sip, see what the secondary

00:06:38.180 --> 00:06:43.210
flavors are and this is how you will evaluate
the beer; so it is not about pounding beers.

00:06:43.210 --> 00:06:44.210
&gt;&gt;Christina: No.

00:06:44.210 --> 00:06:47.990
&gt;&gt;Haille: It is not about drinking it from
the bottom of the can like we all did. It

